      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">Vanadium is a very hard, silvery-grey metal. At room temperature it is unaffected by air and water, but reacts with sulphuric(VI) acid, aqua regia (a mixture of 3 parts of concentrated hydrochloric acid and 1 part of concentrated nitric acid by volume) and hydrofluoric acid. At elevated temperatures vanadium reacts with many non-metals. It combines with oxygen to form oxides in a variety of colours: black  – VO and </text>
